	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />And I am using the admin status to ban spammers' accounts right before I delete all their posts. But every time I am promoted, I learn of a higher access level that I don't yet have. Currently I know of the following:
<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>FTPer </li><li>Administrator (e.g. myself) </li><li>Moderator </li><li>User </li><li>Guest </li></ol>
<br />As far as I can tell, only FTPers can install tools that prevent spam robots from registering or posting. The only relevant actions that I can find in the phpBB 2 admin control panel are to 1. ban accounts that have already spammed (which I am doing) and 2. turn off automatic confirmation of all newly registered accounts.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
